description: Stan "The Man" Lee scripts the fantabulous FANTASTIC FOUR from the days of yore in his own often imitated, but never duplicated fashion! Everyone from the Fearless Front Facers to the Quite 'Nuff Sayers will be here, so don't be square and miss out on the conclusion of our 12-issue retro run! It's Dr. Doom vs. Galactus and the FF vs. Dr. Doom, with the fate of the world, nay, the universe, in the balance! Â
name: Victor von Doom, Emperor of Earth!

volume.name: Fantastic Four: The World's Greatest Comics Magazine

description: A mysterious figure is telling tales of the legendary Guy Gardner's descendants. One tale features a lonely gunslinger on a far off planet trying to survive a girl gang. Another is a heroic young boy who gets swept up into deadly danger. After the tales are done, it turns out the teller is Guy himself talking with his daughter.
name: Hypersensitive: A Change For All Reasons; See My Finger, See My Thumb, See My Fist? You Better Run!; The Gardner Gals in Dateless In A One Gender Town

description: The super-villainy of Kang the Conqueror... unleashed at last! In a classic contest, the Grandmaster and Kang pit the Avengers against the Squadron Sinister and the wartime Invaders! And when the self-proclaimed "Ultimate Kang" sets out to conquer his alternate-reality counterparts, only one force can possibly halt his mad march: himself! Plus: Kang takes on Thor and the Hulk! Collecting Avengers #69-71 and #267-269, Thor #140, and Hulk #135.
name: TPB

description:
Supergirl and Lex Luthor lead Team Luthor into the streets of Metropolis to take the city back from the criminals who've come out in full force since Superman's demise.

Notes:

  • "- - The Future of Metropolis!" written by Roger Stern, penciled by June Brigman, inked by Jackson Guice and Dennis Janke, colored by Glenn Whitmore and lettered by Albert De Guzman.
  • "Shelter" written by Louise Simonson, penciled and inked by Denis Roder, colored by Glenn Whitmore and lettered by Albert De Guzman.
  • Pinup #1 by John Byrne.
  • Pinup #2 by Art Thibert.
  • Pinup #3 by Kerry Gammill and Bob Wiacek.
  • Pinup #4 by Tom Grummett and Doug Hazlewood.
  • "DC Universe" one page text piece featuring "Luthor Fills the Void" in regards to Supergirl/Lex Luthor Special #1. and "DC Bullets" featuring Kevin Dooley popping the question to Tammy Brown, Brian Augustyn posed for the cover of Lex Luthor: The Unauthorized Biography #1, Lobo meets Valor in Valor #4 and Mark Waid just missed his chance to appear as a contestant on You Bet Your Life. Artwork: Team Luthor Brigman and Guice, Superman(?) by Guice and Rodier, Lobo/Valor by Bright and Scott and Kevin Dooley by Ordway and Janke.
  • Cameo flashback appearances by Thorn, Gangbuster, Eradicator, Doomsday, Brainiac, Auron and Guardian.
  • Matrix forms herself into Lucy Ricardo, Princess Leia, Unknown and Lex Luthor's mom in hopes of cheering him up.
name: - - The Future of Metropolis! / Shelter

description: Matrix, an angel, has lost her way in her mission of caring for human souls. Wanting to disassociate from humanity, she is taken down a road of self-discovery that ultimately brings her closer to one soul than any other, that of Linda Danvers. Along the way, Matrix finds aid (and obstacles) from several other members of the DC Universe, including Zauriel, the Phantom Stranger, Aquaman, Clark Kent and the Spectre. Â
name: Supergirl: Wings
